<subSubSection id="7BB36558FF9B1D5279BAF931FDF509D0" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="322" pageId="12" pageNumber="321" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="331636D3FF9B1D5379BAF931FAA60F49" blockId="12.[884,1368,1727,1816]" pageId="12" pageNumber="321">
Family 
<taxonomicName id="F4A94D50FF9B1D5379E7F931FAE10E86" authority="A. H. Clark, 1908 b" authorityName="A. H. Clark" authorityYear="1908" box="[982,1344,1727,1752]" class="Crinoidea" family="Tropiometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Comatulida" pageId="12" pageNumber="321" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">
<emphasis id="01DDEAC1FF9B1D5379E7F931FBDC0E86" bold="true" box="[982,1149,1727,1751]" pageId="12" pageNumber="321">Tropiometridae</emphasis>
A. H. 
<bibRefCitation id="57384B22FF9B1D537E8EF931FAE10E86" author="Clark, A. H." box="[1215,1344,1727,1751]" pageId="12" pageNumber="321" pagination="125 - 136" refId="ref17651" refString="Clark, A. H. 1908 b. New genera of unstalked crinoids. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 21: 125 - 136." type="journal article" year="1908">Clark, 1908b</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
27. 
<taxonomicName id="F4A94D50FF9B1D5379A9F96EFAF90EA9" authority="(Hara, 1895)" baseAuthorityName="Hara" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[920,1368,1759,1784]" class="Crinoidea" family="Tropiometridae" genus="Tropiometra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Comatulida" pageId="12" pageNumber="321" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="subSpecies" species="afra" subSpecies="macrodiscus">
<emphasis id="01DDEAC1FF9B1D5379A9F96EFB730EA6" bold="true" box="[920,1234,1759,1784]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="321">Tropiometra afra macrodiscus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="57384B22FF9B1D537EEEF96EFAF10EA9" author="Hara, J." box="[1247,1360,1760,1784]" pageId="12" pageNumber="321" pagination="115 - 116" refId="ref18519" refString="Hara, J. 1895. Description of a new species of Comatula. Antedon macrodiscus, n. sp. Zoological Magazine, Tokyo 7: 115 - 116." type="journal article" year="1895">Hara, 1895</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
[Japanese name: Oh-umishida]
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="331636D3FF9B1D52797FF8CCFDF509D0" blockId="12.[820,1432,1857,2077]" lastBlockId="13.[156,768,198,775]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="322" pageId="12" pageNumber="321">
<emphasis id="01DDEAC1FF9B1D53797FF8CCFC770F0B" bold="true" box="[846,982,1858,1882]" pageId="12" pageNumber="321">Morphology.</emphasis>
Centrodorsal thick discoidal, 
<quantity id="F4519B36FF9B1D537F7CF8CCFA360F08" box="[1357,1431,1858,1882]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.3" pageId="12" pageNumber="321" unit="mm" value="7.3">7.3 mm</quantity>
across; polar area flat, 0.7 times of centrodorsal diameter. Cirri stout, XXXIV, up to 37 segments, 
<quantity id="F4519B36FF9B1D537EDDF80DFA910FCB" box="[1260,1328,1923,1947]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="12" pageNumber="321" unit="mm" value="37.0">37 mm</quantity>
long, arranged in two, partly three rows; segments broader than long, without aboral ornamentation excepting opposing spine. Radials exposed at distal corners. IBr series composed of 2 ossicles. Arms 
<quantity id="F4519B36FF9B1D537E37F78BFBDE004D" box="[1030,1151,2053,2077]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.021" pageId="12" pageNumber="321" unit="mm" value="10210.0">10, 210 mm</quantity>
long, remarkably massive, 
<quantity id="F4519B36FF9A1D527AADFF48FF75088F" box="[156,212,198,222]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="322" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
at first syzygy; brachial short, with distal ends almost parallel; first arm syzygy at br 
<subScript id="AF2D3496FF9A1D527BE7FF7CFE510951" attach="left" box="[470,496,242,256]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="322">3+4</subScript>
; distal intersyzygial interval 14â€“23. Comparative pinnule length P 
<subScript id="AF2D3496FF9A1D527875FE9DFDED0970" attach="left" box="[580,588,275,289]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="322">1</subScript>
&lt;P 
<subScript id="AF2D3496FF9A1D52785EFE9DFDD60970" attach="left" box="[623,631,275,289]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="322">2</subScript>
&lt;P 
<subScript id="AF2D3496FF9A1D5278AAFE9DFD020970" attach="right" box="[667,675,275,289]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="322">3</subScript>
&gt;P 
<subScript id="AF2D3496FF9A1D5278F7FE9DFD6F0970" attach="left" box="[710,718,275,289]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="322">4</subScript>
=P 
<subScript id="AF2D3496FF9A1D5278C0FE9CFD580971" attach="left" box="[753,761,274,288]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="322">5</subScript>
; proximal pinnules with ridge on basal segments; distal pinnules with aboral ridge, making profiles triangular. Disk stellate, three times as wide as centrodorsal.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7BB36558FF9A1D527A84FE04FD5E09B2" pageId="13" pageNumber="322" type="description">
<paragraph id="331636D3FF9A1D527A84FE04FDCB0993" blockId="13.[156,768,198,775]" pageId="13" pageNumber="322">
<emphasis id="01DDEAC1FF9A1D527A84FE04FEAD09F3" bold="true" box="[181,268,394,418]" pageId="13" pageNumber="322">Posture.</emphasis>
Hiding on underside of overhangs, but sometimes fully exposed, forming simple arm fans.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="331636D3FF9A1D527A84FE44FD5E09B2" blockId="13.[156,768,198,775]" box="[181,767,458,483]" pageId="13" pageNumber="322">
<emphasis id="01DDEAC1FF9A1D527A84FE44FED309B3" bold="true" box="[181,370,458,482]" pageId="13" pageNumber="322">Coloration in life.</emphasis>
Uniformly dark brown or dark orange.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7BB36558FF9A1D527A84FE65FD810A15" pageId="13" pageNumber="322" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="331636D3FF9A1D527A84FE65FD810A15" blockId="13.[156,768,198,775]" pageId="13" pageNumber="322">
<emphasis id="01DDEAC1FF9A1D527A84FE65FEE00A52" bold="true" box="[181,321,491,515]" pageId="13" pageNumber="322">Distribution.</emphasis>
Sadogashima Island, 
<collectingCountry id="4BBE7643FF9A1D527800FE62FDC80A52" box="[561,617,492,515]" name="Japan" pageId="13" pageNumber="322">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="57384B22FF9A1D52784CFE65FEBA0A75" author="Honma, Y. &amp; Kitami, T." pageId="13" pageNumber="322" pagination="7 - 81" refId="ref18583" refString="Honma, Y. and Kitami, T. 1978. Fauna and flora in the waters adjacent to the Sado Marine Biological Station, Niigata University. Annual Report of the Sado Marine Biological Station, Niigata University 8: 7 - 81." type="journal article" year="1978">Honma and Kitami 1978</bibRefCitation>
) to eastern Malay Peninsula (
<bibRefCitation id="57384B22FF9A1D52787DFD82FD540A75" author="Lane, D. J. W. &amp; Marsh, L. M. &amp; VandenSpiegel, D. &amp; Rowe, F. W. E." box="[588,757,524,548]" pageId="13" pageNumber="322" pagination="459 - 493" refId="ref19024" refString="Lane, D. J. W., Marsh, L. M., VandenSpiegel, D., and Rowe, F. W. E. 2000. Echinoderm fauna of the South China Sea: an inventory and analysis of distribution patterns. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, Supplement 8: 459 - 493." type="journal article" year="2000">
Lane 
<emphasis id="01DDEAC1FF9A1D5278B6FD82FD130A75" box="[647,690,524,548]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="322">et al</emphasis>
. 2000
</bibRefCitation>
). Ogasawara Islands (A. H. 
<bibRefCitation id="57384B22FF9A1D527B93FDA2FDB40A15" author="Clark, A. H." box="[418,533,556,580]" pageId="13" pageNumber="322" pagination="1 - 47" refId="ref18121" refString="Clark, A. H. 1947. A monograph of the existing crinoids. Volume 1. The comatulids. Part 4 b. - Superfamily Mariametrida (concluded- the family Colobometridae) and superfamily Tropiometrida (except families Thalassometridae and Charitometridae). Bulletin of the United States National Museum 82: i - vii + 1 - 473, pls 1 - 47." type="journal article" year="1947">Clark 1947</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7BB36558FF9A1D527A84FDC3FD510B56" pageId="13" pageNumber="322" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="331636D3FF9A1D527A84FDC3FD510B56" blockId="13.[156,768,198,775]" pageId="13" pageNumber="322">
<emphasis id="01DDEAC1FF9A1D527A84FDC3FEB80A34" bold="true" box="[181,281,589,613]" pageId="13" pageNumber="322">Remarks.</emphasis>
This large species is easily recognized by its massive 10 arms. Within the species, subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="F4A94D50FF9A1D527889FDE0FF790AF7" authorityName="Hara" authorityYear="1895" class="Crinoidea" family="Antedonidae" genus="Antedon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Comatulida" pageId="13" pageNumber="322" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="macrodiscus">
<emphasis id="01DDEAC1FF9A1D527889FDE0FF790AF7" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="322">macrodiscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is regarded as a northern form, however there is no clear morphological difference to distinguish it from the nomenotypical subspecies, 
<taxonomicName id="F4A94D50FF9A1D527B85FD5EFF740B56" authority="afra (Hartlaub, 1890)" authorityName="afra (Hartlaub" authorityYear="1890" baseAuthorityName="Hartlaub" baseAuthorityYear="1890" class="Crinoidea" family="Tropiometridae" genus="Tropiometra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Comatulida" pageId="13" pageNumber="322" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="subSpecies" species="afra" subSpecies="afra">
<emphasis id="01DDEAC1FF9A1D527B85FD5EFD2F0AB6" box="[436,654,719,743]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="322">Tropiometra afra afra</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="57384B22FF9A1D5278AFFD41FF6F0B56" author="Hartlaub, C." pageId="13" pageNumber="322" pagination="168 - 187" refId="ref18550" refString="Hartlaub, C. 1890. Beitrag zur Kenntniss der Comatuliden-Fauna des Indischen Archipels. Nachrichten von der Koniglichen Gesellschaft der Wissenschaften und der Georgs-August-Universitat zu Gottingen 5: 168 - 187." type="journal article" year="1890">Hartlaub, 1890</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
which is distributed southward from the 
<collectingCountry id="4BBE7643FF9A1D527849FD61FD4C0B56" box="[632,749,751,775]" name="Philippines" pageId="13" pageNumber="322">Philippines</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
